THE four twins met some years ago at Lion King auditions and that’s how their friendship started. And they’ve taken it to the next level, creating growth on their art projects. Imbewu stars Nokubonga and Nokwanda Khuzwayo (36), as well as Vuyelwa and Vuyokazi Tshona (29), are four twins who have made their mark on the entertainment scene. Nokubonga is known as Zakithi Bhengu, the passionate businesswoman in Imbewu and her sister Nokwanda is known as Futhi Bhengu in the e.TV telenovela. Vuyokazi plays Buhle Bhengu on the show, while her sister Vuyelwa is travelling the world with Disney’s The Lion King International Tour as singer and actress. The two sets of twins believe God united them to do great things. “We are talented twins and have a lot in common. That’s the perfect part of our friendship. We believe God united us with purpose,” said Vuyokazi. ALSO READ | UNATHI LEAVES SOCIAL MEDIA DROOLING Their friendship is not just about meeting for drinks and having a good time, but also about developing their craft as artists,which led them to form jazz group, Amawele Square (A2). The group recently released a song titled Isidwaba. Nokubonga said: “It’s good to surround yourself with people who understand your purpose and vision. My friends and I understand each other. We have the same goal. To get into music was our common goal and we did it together.” She said Isidwaba represents the true definition of being African. “I think being an African is a privilege, a blessing that we must celebrate. Africans are unique and strong and it is important for us to be proud of ourselves and promote our culture. Isidwaba represents our tradition and culture,” she said.